Moreover, in Kerala there are no government or NGO efforts to improve family relationships or marital satisfaction. As result, a large chunk of families become susceptible to domestic issues at some point in their married life.

However, one cannot deny the advantages of allowing divorces in cases where couples remain stuck in unhappy wedded relationships and have characters and options to adapt to singlehood.

The writer is Adviser (Nirmal Bang) on research in Banking and Finance and member of The TRIVANDRUM Indian Social Science Research Council.
